sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2185007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: S.ferax alpha amylase w/ cyc promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part, designed and submitted by the 2016 Broad Run iGEM Team, contains an gene from the fungus S.ferax that codes for an alpha amylase enzyme. This composite part contains a constitutive promoter, coding sequence, kozak sequence, a mating factor secretion tag, and a terminator. The amylase enzyme can be expressed by cloning this part into a plasmid without a promoter built in (such as the S.cerevisiae vector pRS426).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Broad Run iGEM Team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The coding sequence of this part comes from the fungus S.ferax
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Codon optimized for S.cerevisiae, EcoR1 and Spe1 sites removed.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K392003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Engineered 'cyc100 promoter' of Saccharomyces cerevisiae with Kozak sequence attached downstream.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tadashi Nakamura, Shuhei Yasumoto, Takahiro Saka, Saya Kakuda

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2185006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a coding sequence for the alpha amylase enzyme from the fungus S.ferax.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Marissa Sumathipala
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the genome of the fungus S.ferax.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Codon optimized for S.cerevisiae, kpn and spe sites removed.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MFa1-Secre
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Secretion tag from yeast α-factor mating pheromone (MFα1)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the secretion signal peptide for the yeast α-mating factor. This signal peptide directs the secretion of the produced protein, and therefore allows for the exportation of it. This peptides are cleaved once the protein is in the lumen of the ER.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gim??nez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Prepro-a-factorHas a Cleavable Signal Sequence [Water et al 1987]

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K165002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The kozak sequence acts as a eukaryotic RBS. It is cloned directly between a promoter and coding region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski
